  "texts": [
    "This approach ultimately provided simulated vibration data that not only fits the measured data but also complies with physical laws.",
    "As shown in the (a)-(d) data in Fig. 11 by feeding real-time inputs from the accelerometer into the simulation digital twin model, errors are minimized to achieve the most accurate updates of the digital twin model.",
    "(a)-(d) represent data for normal elevator vibration, jump vibration, start-stop vibration, and acuteness vibration, respectively.",
    "The figure illustrates the comparison between actual measurements and simulated results for these four types of data.",
    "Compared with the measured data, it can be seen that the simulated digital twin data clearly shows the key features of the actual fault condition."
